cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Agent Runtime Assurance (ARA) Control Family"
message: "If you reference this work, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - name: "Amworkplace Ltd (BoundaryAI)"
version: "0.1-draft"
date-released: "2026-06-28"
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://github.com/skvcool-rgb/agent-runtime-assurance"
repository-code: "https://github.com/skvcool-rgb/agent-runtime-assurance"
abstract: >-
  A vendor-neutral control family (ARA-1 through ARA-8) for deterministic,
  tamper-evident, independently-verifiable runtime assurance of AI agents. The
  software-agent port of aviation Run-Time Assurance (RTA / ASTM F3269), proposed as
  a contribution to the NIST AI Agent Standards Initiative (CAISI), the OWASP GenAI
  Agentic Security Initiative, and ISO/IEC JTC1 SC42.
keywords:
  - AI agents
  - runtime assurance
  - agentic security
  - AI governance
  - prompt injection
  - NIST AI RMF
  - OWASP
  - ISO 42001
